
=Description=

Vasilis Kostakis et al. :

"Small-scale farmers rarely find
appropriate machinery to support their work. So, several individuals and communities of smallscale farmers from all around the world design and manufacture their agricultural tools (Giotitsas
2019). They share their designs as a digital commons. The open-source agricultural tools can be
locally adapted and manufactured by the farmers in physical spaces (makerspaces). Cosmolocal
initiatives, such as 

#L’Atelier Paysan from France, 
#Farm Hack from the US, 
#Tzoumakers from Greece and 
#Nyamdrel Zo’Sa from Bhutan, 

have connected and created synergies by improving the same digital commons."


=More information=

* Source: Kostakis, V., Vragoteris, V., Lal Acharja, I. (2021). Can peer production
democratize technology and society? A critical review of the critiques. Futures,
131.

